arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into four series: Arts and Sciences, Engineering, and SMFA Bulletins; Graduate School of Arts and Sciences Bulletins; Announcement of courses and course descriptions; and Summer School Bulletins.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Arts and Sciences and Engineering Bulletins, 1942 -- 2020. Tufts University. Digital Collections and Archives. Medford, MA.

processinfo.head: Processing status
processinfo.p: This collection is processed and open for research. In 2011, this collection was renamed and reprocessed to provide greater clarity between the combined bulletins and the individual Arts, Sciences, and Engineering bulletins. 2017-2019 accessions processed by Leah Edelman in 2017-2019. Digital objects were stabilized and ingested. A file-level inventory was created, and series-level description as well as the finding aid was updated at the time of processing.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: Tufts Combined Catalogs, Bulletins and Course Announcements, 1854-1970. Tufts University. Digital Collections and Archives. Medford, MA.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of the catalogs and bulletins from 1970 to the present for the School of Arts and Sciences and the School of Engineering, both at the undergraduate and graduate levels. As of 2018, bulletins for the SMFA are also included in this collection. Bulletins include school descriptions, admissions requirements, degree requirements, course descriptions, and rosters of faculty.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproductions and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish.

did.unittitle: Arts and Sciences, Engineering, and SMFA Bulletins

physdesc.extent: Of the 36 digital objects in this series, 30 have extent information and comprise 193.2 MB.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: A course bulletin for the Arts and Sciences published since 1969. Colleges that fall under the school are inconsistent but may include College of Liberal Arts, College of Engineering , College of Special Studies, Jackson School, Boston School of Occupational Therapy, and Graduate School of Arts and Sciences. See series 002 for the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences individual publication. Includes school descriptions, admissions requirements, degree requirements, course descriptions, and rosters of faculty. As of 2018, course bulletins for the SMFA are included in this series.
